commentTextItems.html: hits the ball back past the bowler, Dawlat doesn't time that one and only get a single. Ireland win by 12 runs.

commentPostTextItems.html: Phew, you are going to have to give us a second to recover from that ending.
Well what a match today was, big hitting from both teams meant that over 500 runs were scored in the day.
Lots of exciting bowling and fielding with the weather playing its part and giving us a beautiful summers day here in Stormont.
Plenty of the Afghan batsmen managed to get in, with 5 of them scoring over 30. Yet every time that they looked like getting ahead in the chase they lost wickets.
The killer being losing three wickets in three balls towards the end of the innings.
Dawlat certainly livened up the crowd with his fantastic 31 off 15 balls, but they had left him too much to do.
O'Brien ended up with three wickets, which isn't a bad way to finish off your 100th ODI.
Yet the wickets were spread around between the bowler. With only McBrine not taking a wicket.
Today will be Ed Joyce's day, without him Ireland wouldn't have won and levelled the series. What a brillaint series it was between these two team.
Ended 2-2. Feels a shame that there was only 5 games in the series!

There was a number of great performances from both sides, Rashid Arman looks a great talent and played well in every game. Ed Joyce for his two centuries has been named player of the series. So Congratulations to him.
The Afghanistan tour of Europe continues, travelling to the Netherlands for an Intercontinental four day game.
For Ireland, comes Pakistan, on August 18th in Dublin. So please join us then.
So thanks for following my commentary over the series, its been great to commentate on it.
This is Justin Smyth saying goodnight from a sunlit Stormont. Goodnight

commentTextItems.html: hits the ball back over the bowlers head and it goes all the way. That's a cracking shot
overpitches and Dawlat drives the ball through extra cover, lovely shot from the number 10
hits the ball back over the bowlers head, goes straight and it isn't going to be stopped
its wide of off-stump and Dawlat misses, 28 off four now. Not going to happen I guess
hits the ball down to long-on, Yamin had run down to the other end and Dawlat sent him back
goes down the legside and Poynter can't stop it. 28 needed off 6
full ball chipped back over the bowlers head, 33 runs needed off the final over. This will be some win if Afghanistan win from here!

commentPostTextItems.html: So don't move anyone, six more balls coming up.....

commentTextItems.html: goes too far outside the offstump again
Dawlat stands and delivers. The balls in the slot from O'Brien and Dawlat hits the ball over the wide long-off boundary
Yamin swings through the ball and it goes towards the mid-wicket boundary. They get Dawlat back strike

commentPostTextItems.html: Dawlat steps away at the last minute and O'Brien still bowls the ball. It knocks over the stumps but Umpire Shamshuddin calls a dead ball

commentTextItems.html: its flat batted to wide long-on and they take the single this time. Pretty strange batting of you ask me
too far outside off
swing and miss outside off-stump
hits the ball in the air over mid-on, Stirling makes a diving attempt for the ball and can't hold on. They didn't bother running, bit wierd that one....
gets some bat on the ball and it goes down to fine leg, they turn down the single. Maybe they think they have more chance with Dawlat batting#
its wide outside off-stump and Yamin leaves the ball? Not quite sure that's whats needed Mr Yamin
its another ball outside off-stump and Yamin can't get anything on it
its fast outside off-stump, Yamin misses with the cut shot
its cut past a diving Porterfield at point, they stop the ball just before the rope

headshotImage.longCaption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Asghar Afghan c sub (GH Dockrell) b McCarthy 32 (64b 1x4 0x6) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Stanikzai gets a short ball and pulls it straight into Dockrell's hands at deep square leg. Its an easy catch in the end

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Nabi b Chase 25 (33b 1x4 1x6) SR: 75.75

dismissalComment.html: it another full ball from Chase, Nabi looks to drive the ball. He misses and the middle stump is smashed out of the ground.

headshotImage.caption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Rashid Khan c O'Brien b Stirling 40 (32b 4x4 1x6) SR: 125

dismissalComment.html: its pulled in the air down towards long leg, O'Brien gets under the ball and takes the catch. That's a big wicket for Ireland there!

dismissalText.commentary: Mirwais Ashraf c Chase b O'Brien 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: its a golden duck for Ashraf, O'Brien takes some pace off the ball and Ashraf hits it a mile in the air. Chase gets under the ball at mid-off and takes the catch

dismissalText.commentary: Najibullah Zadran c Wilson b O'Brien 54 (66b 4x4 1x6) SR: 81.81

dismissalComment.html: yes, yes they can. Najibullah swings the ball towards the square leg boundary. Wilson runs in and takes a simple catch. That's the team hatrick, O'Brien is on a hatrick too!

milestones.description: Zadran and Rashid Khan's 94-run partnership is AFG's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 86 between Samiullah Shinwari and Zadran
This is the highest match aggregate (518) involving teams Ireland & Afghanistan in ODIs
Rahmat Shah has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for AFG, going past Hamid Hassan's record
